title: Cate Brandts New Book 'The F's To God' Is a Playbook to Unlock Divine Energy for Readers
text:
Recent release “The F's To God” from Page Publishing author Cate Brandt hopes to help readers be freed from negative energy.
(PRWEB) October 14, 2015
Brandt, who received her Reiki Master Attunement in 2006, has completed her first published book “The F's To God”: The F stands for 6 words that start with F, i.e. Freedom and Fun. These F words have helped her and will guide you to develop positive life experiences.
“Fear is paralyzing! The time has come for the negative thoughts and limiting beliefs that are instilled in us to be liberated,” Brandt said. “This book, ‘The F’s to God,’ may help people see their lives in a uniquely energetic way. Divine energy needs to flow freely on this planet in order to survive. People can use the tools in this book to help divine energy flow to occur.”
Published by New York City-based Page Publishing, Brandt’s motivational work talks about how with the help of Archangels, and through her Reiki Master Attunement, she is able to sense issues that people have in all four facets of their being (emotional, mental, physical, and spiritual).
The author’s encounters presented in this book can help readers to better understand their own experiences. Anyone who has had a paranormal experience or lost a loved one, and military personnel who have been overseas or experienced multi-deaths, may consider reading this book to gain a better understanding of non-divine energy.
Readers who wish to experience this inspiring work can purchase “The F’s To God” at bookstores everywhere, or online at the Apple iTunes store, Amazon, Google Play or Barnes and Noble.
For additional information or media inquiries, contact Page Publishing at 866-315-2708.
About Page Publishing
Page Publishing is a traditional New York based full-service publishing house that handles all of the intricacies involved in publishing its authors’ books, including distribution in the world’s largest retail outlets and royalty generation. Page Publishing knows that authors need to be free to create - not bogged down with complicated business issues like eBook conversion, establishing wholesale accounts, insurance, shipping, taxes and the like. Its roster of authors can leave behind these tedious, complex and time consuming issues, and focus on their passion: writing and creating. Learn more at http://www.pagepublishing.com .
